In a microwavable bowl, mix water and margarine (cut into pieces). Stir in stuffing mix and cover with a microwavable lid. Cook on HIGH for 8 to 10 minutes. Fluff with fork. Place eggplant, zucchini, tomato, onion into a large skillet. Season with thyme, salt, and pepper. Cook and stir over medium low heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F ( 175 degrees C). Grease a 2 quart casserole dish. Layer vegetables, cheese, and stuffing in the dish until all ingredients have been used, ending with cheese. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.